      "subcategory": "asic",
      "summary": "The validation of multi-year AI compute demand, driven by memory scarcity and the pull-forward of the HBM TAM, is highly positive for AI accelerator and custom silicon providers. Nvidia, AMD (MI-series), Broadcom, and Marvell are key beneficiaries, with competitive differentiation increasingly tied to memory architecture, HBM allocation, and packaging integration.",
